    • getIconByPropName

      public static ImageIcon getIconByPropName(String propName)
      Fetch an ImageIcon resource by i18n property name. For lookup, the given property name will be converted such that all period (".") characters will be translated to underscores. For example, "camera.util.focus.near" will result in a lookup of "camera_util_focus_near". This lookup scheme can be useful, for example, to implicitly associate JButton icons with IAction IDs.
      Parameters:
      propName - The property name to use.
      Returns:
      The requested ImageIcon, or null if not found.
